<section id="intro" class="section-row">
  <div class="section-label">
    <div class="section-label-inner">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info section-icon icon-wobble"></i>
      <span class="section-title">Intro</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-content">
    <button class="scroll-top-btn" aria-label="Scroll to top">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up"></i>
    </button>
    <div class="section-content-inner">
      <h5 class="content-heading">A Little About Me</h5>
      <p>
        I've always enjoyed creating. As a child, I made drawings (scribbles?) for anyone who would take them.
        As time went on, my skill with pencil and paper improved. In high school, I became interested in computer
        programming, attracted by the ability to create new things with new tools.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over 20 years later, I still get the same satisfaction from building things. I'm drawn to the complexity
        of full-stack development — the craft of designing interfaces people enjoy using, and the architecture of
        systems that hold up under real-world pressure. Lately, much of that work has been custom MES/ERP systems,
        where those old artistic instincts turn out to be surprisingly useful.
      </p>
      <p>
        I take the mentoring side of senior development seriously too. There's something genuinely rewarding about
        helping a junior developer click with a concept they've been wrestling with.
      </p>
      <p>I keep busy and pick up new skills along the way.</p>
      <p>I still draw from time to time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .content-heading {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
  }

  :is(.section-row:hover, .section-row.nav-activated) .content-heading {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
  }

  :is(.section-row:hover, .section-row.nav-activated) p {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
</style>
